  "summary": "Base64-decoded eval payload in router_init.js",
  "details": "router_init.js line 4 passes a base64-encoded string through Buffer.from(..., 'base64').toString() and into eval(). This is the canonical obfuscated-payload-execution pattern: the package decodes a hidden blob and runs it as JavaScript at load time. There is no legitimate reason for a helper/router module to base64-decode and eval its own logic; the construction exists to hide the real behavior from review and to allow the author to ship arbitrary code that executes whenever this module is required. Any installer that requires this package executes the decoded payload in their Node process, with full access to environment variables, filesystem, and network.",
